        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down.</hi> | Beckenham | <hi rend="print">Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Nov. 9<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I write a line to thank you for your letter &amp; say how very glad I am to hear that I was partly mistaken about the Professorship.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> What you say does not make the slightest differences in my wishes.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>Herr. Hoffmann of Stuttgart has applied to me, since I wrote to you, for the right of Translation.— I have simply told Herr Koch that I had communicated with you on the subject of my next book, &amp; it will rest with you to decide whether to prefer him.—<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>In Haste | My dear Sir | Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 Beckenham] <hi rend="italic">before del</hi> ‘<hi rend="italic">Bromley.</hi>’ </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6974.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. V. Carus, 6 November 1869</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6974.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. V. Carus, 6 November 1869</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD wanted Carus to translate <hi rend="italic">Descent.</hi></note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">No letter from <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5923.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Carl Hoffmann</ref>, a publisher in Stuttgart, has been found. The most recent extant letter to the publisher <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2732.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Eduard Koch</ref> is that of 4 November 1869.</note>
